My aim in this paper is to provide a whirlwind tour of early literature addressing hydraulic control of rotating fluids and briefly try my own hand at estimating whether certain setups are hydraulically controlled

* Sources
  - definition of hydraulic:
    - at the risk of being cliche: denoting, relating to, or operated by a liquid moving in a confined space under pressure. 
  - Whitehead 1973 https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/abs/10.1080/03091927409365790
    - aim not to produce detailed models but understanding the most elementary schemes
    - laboratory experiments
    - cool estimates of real life sills
  - Gill 2006 https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/journal-of-fluid-mechanics/article/abs/hydraulics-of-rotatingchannel-flow/9F60E4E7F489AB8B0E6A29F722F1913F
  - Zhao 2019
  - Pratt and Armi https://doi.org/10.1007/BF00876224
  - the book andrew sent


